languages.text: «No finja entender lo que es la pérdida, maestra Kibellah. Su mente está demasiado dañada como para sentir empatía. Vuelva a sus tareas».
languages.original_text: "Do not pretend to have any understanding of loss, Mistress Kibellah. Your mind is too warped to be capable of empathy. Return to your duties."

languages.text: 「キベラ様、喪失感を理解したような振りはおやめください。あなたの心は歪みすぎていて、共感することはできません。職務にお戻りなさい」
languages.original_text: "Do not pretend to have any understanding of loss, Mistress Kibellah. Your mind is too warped to be capable of empathy. Return to your duties."

languages.text: “还是不要假装懂得何谓‘失去’了，绮贝菈女士。你的思想过于扭曲，根本没办法产生同理心，还是去做你的本职工作吧。”
languages.original_text: "Do not pretend to have any understanding of loss, Mistress Kibellah. Your mind is too warped to be capable of empathy. Return to your duties."

languages.text: "Tut nicht so, als würdet Ihr verstehen, was Verlust bedeutet, Meisterin Kibellah. Euer Verstand ist zu verdreht, um Empathie zu empfinden. Kehrt zu Euren Pflichten zurück."
languages.original_text: "Do not pretend to have any understanding of loss, Mistress Kibellah. Your mind is too warped to be capable of empathy. Return to your duties."

languages.text: « Ne prétendez pas comprendre ce qu'est le deuil, maîtresse Kibellah. Votre esprit est bien trop tordu pour être capable de la moindre empathie. Retournez à votre poste. »
languages.original_text: "Do not pretend to have any understanding of loss, Mistress Kibellah. Your mind is too warped to be capable of empathy. Return to your duties."
